@startuml
title Firebase Authentication - Google Sign-In (Popup Flow)

actor User
participant "Web App\n(Frontend)" as App
participant "Firebase JS SDK" as FirebaseSDK
participant "Google Auth Server" as Google
participant "Firebase Auth Handler\n<project>.firebaseapp.com" as Handler

User -> App: Click "Login with Google"
App -> FirebaseSDK: firebase.auth().signInWithPopup(googleProvider)

FirebaseSDK -> Google: Open popup to Google OAuth\n(client_id, scopes, redirect_uri)

Google -> User: Show Google Login & Consent
User -> Google: Select account / grant permission

Google -> Handler: Redirect with auth response\n(code or credential)\n?apiKey=PUBLIC_API_KEY
Handler -> FirebaseSDK: Process redirect result\nvia /__/auth/handler

FirebaseSDK -> Google: Exchange code for tokens\n(if required)
Google --> FirebaseSDK: id_token, access_token, user info

FirebaseSDK -> App: Return Firebase User object\n+ ID token
App -> User: Logged in successfully
@enduml